1
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:38,620
"The orange tree is in his yard,
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

2
00:00:38,620 --> 00:00:38,640
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

3
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:41,180
but its oranges
keep falling into my yard."
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

4
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:41,280
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

5
00:00:41,340 --> 00:00:45,100
At first, I was stunned
when I heard the title.

6
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:47,900
"What kind of title is this?
Why is it so long?"

7
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:48,980
"The orange tree is in his yard,

8
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,920
but its oranges
keep falling into my yard."

9
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,100
That's a mouthful, right?

10
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,580
It took me a while to remember it.

11
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:55,420
But once I broke it into beats,
I could remember it.

12
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:56,540
Here it goes—

13
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:58,240
The orange tree / is in his yard /

14
00:00:58,280 --> 00:01:00,360
but its oranges /
keep falling into my yard!

15
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:01,720
Now I remember.

16
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,860
-It's pretty straightforward.
-It means exactly that.

17
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:06,780
The oranges fall into the neighbor's yard,

18
00:01:06,820 --> 00:01:09,920
and someone in that house loves eating them.

19
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:12,860
They're really sweet.

20
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:14,680
The orange tree is in my house.

21
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:18,020
But the oranges
fall into the next-door yard.

22
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:18,820
Yes.

23
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:23,420
Also, when I'm not home,
he sneaks in and picks the oranges.

24
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:25,320
Not that.

25
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,820
When I'm home…

26
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:33,280
and every time I think
an orange might fall from the tree,

27
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:34,460
there's already one in the yard.

28
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:37,820
The orange tree
also connects their relationship.

29
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:49,340
Hi. My name's Kanin Siritara. Or just Ko.

30
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,420
Oh boy.

31
00:01:51,540 --> 00:01:54,020
Guess there's more than one Ko
in this school now.

32
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,480
My role is a new student.

33
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:59,560
My family moves around a lot.

34
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,620
We move in next door…

35
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:02,140
Alright.

36
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:03,620
…to Ko Neung.

37
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,320
And my nickname is also Ko.

38
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:09,220
When I show up at school,
since I'm the new kid,

39
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:11,620
so I introduce myself as Ko.

40
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:14,740
But this Ko isn't happy,
so he calls himself Ko Neung (Ko 1),

41
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:16,020
and I become Ko Song (Ko 2).

42
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,320
Because we're both Ko.

43
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:20,120
"Hey, I have to be the only Ko."

44
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,880
"Then you're Ko Song now."

45
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,760
Looks like the neighbor
has a kid your age.

46
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,020
You two could be friends.

47
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:29,320
That dude doesn't look friendly.

48
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,080
I don't like his vibe. At all.

49
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,020
The character of Ko Neung?

50
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:35,660
Well, he's a boy just living his life
day by day.

51
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,740
He's pretty chill.

52
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:39,260
He doesn't really think much about life,
no goals or anything like that.

53
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:43,220
His goal is just to eat oranges
and mess with people every day.

54
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,640
I meet him for the first time at school,

55
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,460
when I introduce myself
in front of the class.

56
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,320
Then I realize—

57
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:51,920
that's the guy who lives next door.

58
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,780
And I even end up sitting next to him.

59
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:57,820
So that's our first meeting at school,
the two Ko's.

60
00:02:57,860 --> 00:03:01,640
At first, Ko Neung is kind of standoffish
because he thinks I'm like a softie.

61
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:04,120
Like he doesn't see us getting along.

62
00:03:04,420 --> 00:03:07,000
After meeting Ko Song,

63
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,000
I don't like him at first,

64
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:13,940
but later Ko Neung
has to stay close to him

65
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:16,680
because of a group assignment at school.

66
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:19,720
I feel like Ko Neung
has this mafia-kid vibe.

67
00:03:19,980 --> 00:03:23,320
Why does he give off a mafia kid vibe?
Acting all tough.

68
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,300
After a while,
I start to get used to his behavior.

69
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:32,540
Their relationship slowly develops
from classmates to close friends,

70
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,860
and from close friends
to something like love,

71
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,820
but they don't really know
what kind of love it is.

72
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:40,680
Since it's set in the '90s,
LGBTQ+ wasn't very openly accepted,

73
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:44,060
so Ko Neung isn't sure
what kind of feelings he has.

74
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:47,620
It's a young, pure kind of love,
nothing too deep.

75
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:52,620
Love from a time
when things weren't fully open yet.

76
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:55,920
So he doubts himself, and Ko Song—

77
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,780
Ko Song probably doubts himself too,

78
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:00,360
like he doesn't think
he should cross that line.

79
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:01,600
You sure you don't?

80
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,360
You've been talking about him nonstop
since Augar was still dry.

81
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:07,720
Should we just corner him
and scare him into joining our group?

82
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:09,320
What kind of nonsense is this?

83
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:12,440
There's no way someone like Ko
would ever let that guy into our group.

84
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:12,960
[PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

85
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:16,440
I play Krittin Yingkhun, nickname Ko.
[PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

86
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:19,920
He's bold, a bit rebellious, playful,
and kind of a punk.

87
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,500
He acts first and thinks later.

88
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:23,900
Not think first, but do first.

89
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,780
What are the similarities
between Ko and me?

90
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,140
Well… almost everything.

91
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:34,680
I'm playful too, just like Ko,
with a lot of energy.

92
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,820
He has this hyper energy.

93
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:42,920
P'AloneNew, the director, said
if my energy is at 100, Ko's is a million.

94
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:46,760
Hey. Keep this in mind, I run this alley.

95
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:51,680
The most delicious oranges for Ko Neung
are the ones from Ko Song's yard.

96
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:54,620
Ko loves oranges,
like a real orange lover.

97
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,340
He can't live without them.

98
00:04:56,380 --> 00:04:58,720
He can eat tons of them.

99
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,220
The challenge with this character?

100
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:03,740
The energy.

101
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,300
It's the hardest part to keep up with.

102
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:08,420
I'm not too worried about other things,
but the energy is really tough.

103
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:12,020
Because Ko's energy is seriously high.

104
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:14,860
If you watch it,
you'll see how high it is.

105
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,820
The energy has to be through the roof.

106
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,380
When I'm in this character,
I have to pace myself well.

107
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,540
So it's pretty hard.

108
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:23,220
I've got to hand it to Ko Neung's role.

109
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:25,340
This character requires a lot of energy.

110
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:29,320
To really nail it,
you need a great deal of energy.

111
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:31,540
Ko Neung is a bit of a punk.

112
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:38,120
He puts on this tough, cool act
to make people think he's a cool kid.

113
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:44,060
I mean, he's a naughty and playful boy
who doesn't think much.

114
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:50,300
He's a kid who doesn't overthink
or think things through all that much.

115
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,600
Ko Neung is a bit of a nuisance,
[KEN KANTHEE as AUGAR]

116
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:58,120
like he wants to be known and popular,
so he acts tough and cool.

117
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:00,220
He's the leader of our gang.

118
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,300
How should I put it?
He's overly confident.

119
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,480
He's daring and bold.

120
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:06,620
He calls himself the leader.
[PAUL TANAN as ACHI]

121
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:09,500
He has to look cool and all.

122
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:10,720
Also…

123
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:14,220
he's lively and kind of adorable.

124
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,260
He's funny.

125
00:06:15,620 --> 00:06:18,720
Ko Neung is playful and stubborn.
[KEATON SITTHITHAT as TLE]

126
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,860
He's quite a character.

127
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:23,520
He's the entertainer of the group.

128
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:33,120
From now on, I'm Ko Neung,

129
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:36,380
and this guy's Ko Song.

130
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:40,820
Lately, since working on this series,
Progress has been studying his role.

131
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:46,320
As I spend time with him,
I see he's just like this character.

132
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:52,520
His playfulness, his personality,
both Ko and Progress—

133
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,020
for example, Ko loves oranges,

134
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:56,540
and Progress has started
to like oranges too.

135
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,240
In so many ways,

136
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:05,920
the way he talks, the way he socializes,
I feel like Progress has become Ko Neung.

137
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:07,320
He's very much alike.

138
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,020
Like exactly alike.

139
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:10,920
I give him that.

140
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:13,020
The cast for this role is spot on.

141
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:14,300
Ko Neung is pretty much alike Progress

142
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:18,960
because Progress is energetic, playful,
and likes to tease others too.

143
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,220
He's like Ko Neung.

144
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:23,080
On set, he likes teasing Paul
and everyone else.

145
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:25,820
He's always at something.

146
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,240
Progress…

147
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:30,140
he's like the leader of the group
that teases me.

148
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,540
He enjoys teasing and annoying me.
He's the one who starts it.

149
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,900
If it's just Progress,
I can handle him just fine.

150
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:39,880
But he brings along his gang—
Augar, August,

151
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,260
and Ko Song.

152
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,460
Well, Ko Song doesn't really join in.

153
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,820
He's nice, like a bestie to me.

154
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:50,620
I feel like Progress is
very skilled and a great actor.

155
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:53,420
He's cheerful,

156
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,980
and his energy never drops.

157
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,900
He never seems tired or sleepy.

158
00:07:57,940 --> 00:08:00,860
When we're in scenes together,
it's really fun.

159
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,760
We get along well.

160
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,520
You okay?

161
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,100
I just got some powder in my eyes.

162
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,720
Here.

163
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,820
Can I call you Orange?

164
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,560
Huh?

165
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,040
You gave me a nickname.

166
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,620
Why can't I give you one too?

167
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:20,540
Sure, but only when we're alone.

168
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:21,980
Actually, Oran—oops!

169
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:27,400
I play Kanin Siritara, nickname Ko.
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG]

170
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:30,600
This Ko is quiet.

171
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:34,060
He doesn't talk much
with people he's not close to,

172
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,880
and he's a good student.

173
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:37,820
The challenge with this character?

174
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:42,220
I feel like he's still a student,
so in a way, he's not too far from me.

175
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:46,320
He has low energy,
but it's not like he has no energy at all.

176
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:49,820
There's something going on inside him.

177
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,420
Ko Song, in my view, is…

178
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:54,420
a nerd, a softie, but not too soft.

179
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:56,540
He's well-behaved.

180
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:59,420
His family moves around a lot,

181
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,420
but they decide to settle here
for a good while.

182
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,800
That's what brings him closer to Ko Neung.

183
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,440
Because Ko Song doesn't really
have close friends,

184
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,160
since he moves around often.

185
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,980
He doesn't like hanging out
with others much.

186
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:10,720
Yeah.

187
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,220
He's a good student.
He even does assignments for me.

188
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:18,020
He does them for every subject,
like my little minion, at first.

189
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:22,460
But later on, he becomes my "bii."

190
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:23,560
"Bii?"

191
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,920
Ko Song is a good kid, a good student,

192
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:30,620
and he just kind of goes along
with whatever Ko Neung wants.

193
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:33,800
He must really like Ko Neung,
enough to spoil him that much,

194
00:09:33,820 --> 00:09:36,020
like he's just willing to put up with him.

195
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,340
Ko Song?

196
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,520
He's really quiet and calm.

197
00:09:39,940 --> 00:09:42,280
Like he doesn't show his feelings at all.

198
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:45,980
And he seems to think things through.
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

199
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:46,440
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

200
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:51,260
He seems mature and responsible,
which is quite different from Ko Neung.

201
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,820
Ko Song is a quiet person.

202
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,480
He keeps his character.

203
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:59,400
He's mature, composed,
and a bit intimidating.

204
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:01,280
I know you're cool,
but cool it down a bit, bro.

205
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,540
(Wow.)

206
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:03,740
Vroom~

207
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:07,100
Almond and—
whoa, they're total opposites.

208
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:14,780
But their way of speaking
and their rhythm are quite similar.

209
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:18,940
As for the character and his real self,
they're quite different in many ways.

210
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:22,520
Because Almond is a bit more resolute,

211
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,380
while Ko Song isn't as much.

212
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:28,220
They're probably on opposite ends.

213
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:36,280
Ko Song seems like a good student,
like the school's poster boy.

214
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:40,320
But I don't think Almond is one.

215
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:43,220
He's a little stubborn and playful.

216
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,020
Right now. / Right now.

217
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,060
Gang… / Gang…

218
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,020
P'Ko / P'Ko

219
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,420
is filming. / is filming.

220
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,020
Meanwhile, we…

221
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:53,920
Gang…

222
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,060
Ginggue (Millipede)

223
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,060
Flapping

224
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,160
Our wings

225
00:10:59,540 --> 00:11:00,380
are

226
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,400
eating.

227
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,620
I think they're quite different.

228
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:10,080
Almond may be quiet like Ko Song,
but he has a playful side.

229
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:15,020
Ko Song is more on the quiet side
and focused on studying like a nerd.

230
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:19,620
Ko Neung is very hyper,
while Ko Song is much calmer.

231
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:24,460
He responds to people in a gentle way,
but Ko Neung is such a tease.

232
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:28,160
In real Songkran,
nobody gently dabs the powder on you.

233
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,620
They just smear it
all over your face in one go.

234
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,640
And the powder gets in your eyes,
your mouth, your nose.

235
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,320
Don't film us.

236
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,720
(Such a star.)

237
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,800
Don't throw water. We're not playing.

238
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,440
Don't you f*cking try to play the hero.

239
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,680
What the hell is wrong with you?

240
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,920
Should we go study in my room?

241
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:07,700
We got to work together again
under the same roof.
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

242
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:07,720
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

243
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,560
Well, we…
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

244
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,120
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

245
