PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

246
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:11,220
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

247
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:14,620
The first day we heard about it,
we were so excited.
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

248
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:14,840
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

249
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,340
Yes.
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

250
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:15,360
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

251
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,880
Honestly, we were really excited.
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

252
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:17,020
[ALMOND POOMSUWAN as KO SONG
PROGRESS PASSAWISH as KO NEUNG]

253
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,900
It's our first series, right?

254
00:12:20,060 --> 00:12:23,180
-Yes.
-Our first series with GMMTV as a pair.

255
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:26,020
We kept asking each other,

256
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,800
"Do you think it's going to be good?"

257
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,140
"What do you think it's going to be like?"

258
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,300
This and that.

259
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,520
Stressed? Were you stressed?

260
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,400
Yes, I was really stressed.

261
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:37,720
It's been a while
since we last worked together.

262
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,620
It's been quite a while.

263
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:39,820
Yes.

264
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:43,620
We don't need to talk much
because we already know each other.

265
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,780
Yeah, we know each other well.

266
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,740
Just from a look,
we know what the other wants.

267
00:12:48,780 --> 00:12:50,460
Yes.

268
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,900
When I look into Progress's eyes,
I feel more focused while filming.

269
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,540
I know what I should do in each situation.

270
00:12:58,580 --> 00:12:59,820
Honestly, I think it's not that different.

271
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:04,240
Progress plays someone
who's quite talkative and cheerful,

272
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:06,520
while Almond is a bit quieter.

273
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,480
So they match well together,

274
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,160
just like their characters,
Ko Neung and Ko Song.

275
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:12,120
They're really, really close.
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

276
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:15,720
They know what each other is
okay with and not okay with.

277
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:18,300
They don't go overboard
when playing around.

278
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:23,580
So I feel like they must be really close
and trust each other a lot.

279
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:43,000
Since this is my debut work with GMMTV,
I want to do it well.

280
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,240
So I told Almond—

281
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,620
"We have to give this our best."

282
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:49,000
"We shouldn't kid around."

283
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,880
Well, we can be goofballs sometimes.
Just don't stress over it too much.

284
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,400
If we're too stressed,

285
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:55,720
we might lose focus on what really matters.

286
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,640
We'd be too stressed
and lose who we really are.

287
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:01,500
So we try to stay chill on set.

288
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:05,220
Since Ko is a chill guy,

289
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:06,620
when I go into a scene,

290
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:09,660
I review the dialogue once or twice
and then just act.

291
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:12,560
I don't want to overthink it,
I just let my feelings lead.

292
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:15,500
So it looks more natural.

293
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,400
Am I stressed? Of course I am.

294
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:21,020
When I read the script,
since Ko Neung is the chatty one,

295
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:22,820
he has a lot of lines.

296
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:25,340
I was like,
"He really loves talking to himself."

297
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:27,920
I understand the role though,
since I'm like that sometimes too,

298
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:29,300
like talking to myself.

299
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:33,420
But I think this series
is quite challenging,

300
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:34,640
especially when it comes to energy.

301
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:37,720
I was worried I might not be able to match
the character's energy.

302
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:40,620
But as we filmed, I thought to myself,
"Oh, I can actually handle this."

303
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:45,020
I want to say that Progress
is really dedicated to his work.

304
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:49,520
He keeps calling me, like,
"Don't forget to read the script."

305
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:52,980
"If you're sick,
don't forget to take your medicine,

306
00:14:53,020 --> 00:14:58,320
or you'll feel unwell on set
and it'll be hard to perform."

307
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:02,480
He's always reminding me,

308
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:06,120
"For this series,
we have to give it our all."

309
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:09,020
"We really have to put everything into it."

310
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,380
He said, "I'm giving it my all,

311
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:13,980
so you have to give it your all
with me too."

312
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:15,100
Yeah.

313
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,400
I think Almond has become
more serious too.

314
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:22,160
Since we're partners,

315
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:25,020
maybe he sees me being serious,
so he becomes more serious as well.

316
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:26,460
We support each other like that.

317
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:30,300
Since we joined GMMTV,
we've talked a lot about many things.

318
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:32,220
Like, "Hey, I'm so excited."

319
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:37,520
We've met a lot of people and tried
to get to know the seniors in the company.

320
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:40,380
And with Almond, we already have
deep talks about many things.

321
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,300
Do you like it when I'm around?

322
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:52,620
Then I'll be your best friend, Augar.

323
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,120
So you won't feel lonely.

324
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:59,900
I play Augar, Thawan Obkit.
[KEN KANTHEE as AUGAR]

325
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:03,920
He's playful, mischievous, and athletic.

326
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:07,860
He's popular with girls,

327
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:10,640
but he's not interested in anyone
in particular.

328
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:15,600
He usually hangs out with his gang—
Ko Neung, August,

329
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:20,560
I think Augar is similar to me
in terms of personality.

330
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:25,420
I also like to tease people,
maybe not as much as Augar.

331
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:27,440
And he plays sports, just like me.

332
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:30,120
That's something we have in common.

333
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,220
The challenge in this series is…

334
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:33,980
