we just know what to do.

414
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:12,820
You just transferred to this school?

415
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:16,400
Yes, my name is Nong Ngor-Ngae.

416
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,420
Nong Ngor-Ngae?

417
00:20:17,460 --> 00:20:18,620
That's right.

418
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:20,400
You have to do our gang's signature pose.

419
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,340
How?

420
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:26,120
This is millepede flapping its wings.

421
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,500
Like this?

422
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:31,280
Flap them.

423
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:43,260
I play Achira Lert-warit,
or nickname Achi.

424
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:47,320
Achi is a good, nerdy kid.

425
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:49,220
He comes from a rich family.

426
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:54,080
In junior high, he didn't have any friends

427
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,820
because he's a homebody
and very attached to his mom.

428
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:57,680
He's a rich, well-behaved kid.

429
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,220
He only starts having friends
in high school,

430
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:00,560
and it's this group.

431
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:05,520
He doesn't really know how to act
since he usually doesn't have many friends.

432
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,720
He's a top student,
a very well-behaved kid.

433
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,420
But after meeting Augar, he starts to…

434
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:12,540
he's still a good kid,

435
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:15,100
but Augar helps open up his world more.

436
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,800
In the series, my character gets bullied
by seniors at school.

437
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,280
Yes, because he's a rich kid.

438
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,640
They extort money from him,

439
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,220
and he doesn't really have much to give.

440
00:21:25,380 --> 00:21:35,120
Achi is a quiet, soft kid who gets bullied
because he doesn't stand up for himself.

441
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:36,080
That's a bit similar to his real self.

442
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,660
But Paul isn't really a soft kid.

443
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:40,660
He plays around with others sometimes.

444
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,800
But Achi is completely quiet.

445
00:21:43,060 --> 00:21:46,180
As for not standing up for himself,
that part is quite similar.

446
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,820
He always gets teased by Progress.

447
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:51,780
Achi is a soft, silver-spoon kid,

448
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:54,580
and also a good student.

449
00:21:54,620 --> 00:21:58,160
He likes to give academic answers,
just like Ko Song.

450
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:01,000
In the series, Achi and my character
are the same type, the nerdy type.

451
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:04,300
They're the kind of kids who are like,
"Come on, let's go to class."

452
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:08,620
"We need to study, the exams are coming."

453
00:22:08,940 --> 00:22:15,900
Achi is like a good friend, puppy-coded.

454
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:20,140
A cute boy who's gentle when playing.

455
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:23,100
He's an easy target for teasing.

456
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,960
I think Paul connects
to this character very easily.

457
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:26,940
Because he's—

458
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:33,800
Paul himself is quite similar to Achi.

459
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:36,060
They have similar personalities.

460
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,980
I'd say they're very alike.

461
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:39,320
The casting is really good,

462
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:40,620
they're really alike.

463
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:41,640
Paul is really lovely.

464
00:22:41,660 --> 00:22:44,220
He's so adorable
it makes you want to tease him.

465
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,040
He's like JUMMO.

466
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:48,060
I just want to pinch him.

467
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,720
P'Paul is really lovely.

468
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:53,320
He's very nice.

469
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,980
I think everyone on set likes him.

470
00:22:55,020 --> 00:22:59,100
When he says something,
you just feel like… aww.

471
00:22:59,580 --> 00:23:04,100
I feel like Paul has high expectations
