490
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:49,340
Please give him some love.
How old are you?

491
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:50,280
15

492
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,700
Is there such a thing in Scotland?

493
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:55,720
This is how he says "Dragon Ball"

494
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,940
How do you say it?

495
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,220
Dragon Ball.

496
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,220
Dragon Ball.

497
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:06,100
Hi, my name is Justin.
I play Thawin Obkit.
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

498
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:06,800
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

499
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,620
Nickname August.
[JUSTIN MOIR as AUGUST]

500
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:11,580
This character is an anime lover.

501
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:13,880
He loves manga like Dragon Ball,
things like that.

502
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:15,220
He's very attached to his friends
and tends to follow them.

503
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:18,240
He's not very brave when it comes to doing
what his friends do,

504
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:22,880
but he still tries to fit into the group.

505
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,100
He's quite different from me.

506
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:29,900
Personally, I'm more quiet.

507
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:35,100
With people I don't know,
I'm very reserved.

508
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:37,020
But if we're talking about
August and Justin,

509
00:24:37,060 --> 00:24:39,240
I think we're very different,

510
00:24:39,260 --> 00:24:44,500
because I don't read manga
or watch anime at all.

511
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:45,820
August…

512
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:47,740
August is a close friend of Ko Neung.

513
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,800
He likes to read Dragon Ball.

514
00:24:50,660 --> 00:24:53,900
He reads it with Ko Neung.
He's one of Ko Neung's minions.

515
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,500
He's Augar's brother.

516
00:24:56,840 --> 00:25:01,300
He just follows Ko Neung in everything,
playful and nuisance, just like him.

517
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:09,620
August in the series is playful,
with a bit of a childish side.

518
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:15,080
Like a kid who plays games
and watches cartoons and anime.

519
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:19,720
But Justin in real life is more mature.

520
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:22,920
He seems more mature than August.

521
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,820
How do you call it? An anime nerd?

522
00:25:25,380 --> 00:25:27,100
A bit over-the-top.

523
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:30,580
He follows Ko Neung a lot,
a very loyal follower.

524
00:25:30,780 --> 00:25:33,720
Unlike Augar, who doesn't
go along with Ko Neung as much.

525
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:37,840
August seems like he'd stand up to people,
but he's also kind of timid

526
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:40,420
since he's into cartoons.

527
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:42,120
He's a bit scared too.

528
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:45,240
We might seem similar,
but we're actually quite different.

529
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:47,400
I'm more of bold, ready to take the hit

530
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:51,020
but August has his fears.

531
00:25:51,060 --> 00:25:54,120
He's really into manga,
a bit of an anime nerd.

532
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:57,340
Tle and August are classmates
who sit next to each other

533
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,380
in the same classroom.

534
00:25:59,620 --> 00:26:03,600
Tle gets teased and annoyed by August

535
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:09,000
sometimes, and as they spend time together,
they become closer.

536
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,620
This is Tle.

537
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:11,740
I'm the class president.

538
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:14,040
He's also Achi's best friend.

539
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:14,780
That's right.

540
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:18,160
Yes. Because I don't want to
hang out with that gang.

541
00:26:18,180 --> 00:26:19,560
I'd rather be with Tle.

542
00:26:19,660 --> 00:26:20,960
Tle is nice.

543
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:21,620
Yes.

544
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:23,700
Yes. And smart too.

545
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:26,100
Here.

546
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:28,320
Is it hot?

547
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,320
Argh, it's hot.

548
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:31,820
Really?

549
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:32,640
Try it.

550
00:26:35,740 --> 00:26:37,300
You'll get hit by this car.

551
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:41,540
-Is that "Rod Bangkap" (RC car)?
-Yes, "Rod Bangkrap"

552
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,120
"Rod Bangkap"

553
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:44,920
"Rod Bangkrap"?

554
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:46,380
"Bangkrap"?

555
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:49,300
I'm being polite here, ending with "krap."

556
00:26:53,220 --> 00:26:54,100
I'm a newcomer.

557
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,800
Look if I can punch him.

558
00:27:02,060 --> 00:27:03,020
I'm Keaton.

559
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:07,080
I play Techin Rungcharoenchai,
or nickname Tle.

560
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:13,900
This character has been with this group
since junior high,

561
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:18,920
but they only become close in high school.

562
00:27:18,940 --> 00:27:20,720
They grow closer later on.

563
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:27,180
He feels like he wants to help his friends
and have a role in the group.

564
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:29,900
Someone else is supposed to be
the class president,

565
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:36,820
but August helps vote for me
because I secretly signal to him

566
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,540
that I want the position.

567
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:41,320
So he helps me.

568
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:42,340
The challenge?

569
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:45,300
Probably my own experience.

570
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:50,760
I'm new, and this is my first series,
so I'm excited.

571
00:27:50,780 --> 00:27:55,720
A bit nervous too,
so I have to study this role quite a lot.

572
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:59,020
There are some similarities,
but not that many.

573
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:03,440
In scenes, he's a quiet kid
who reads books,

574
00:28:03,460 --> 00:28:07,080
but once he's out of the scene,
he's completely different.

575
00:28:07,260 --> 00:28:11,860
He becomes loud and full of energy.

576
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:15,620
Before joining GMMTV,
we already knew each other.

577
00:28:15,660 --> 00:28:18,580
We'd worked together before,

578
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:20,820
so we're already pretty close.

579
00:28:20,860 --> 00:28:23,720
Now that
we're working together again here,

580
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:28,680
we talk more and have gotten even closer.

581
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:30,600
Working with P'Keaton?

582
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,040
It's really fun.

583
00:28:32,260 --> 00:28:34,700
We were already close before,

584
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:37,560
and after coming here together,
we've become even closer.

585
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:39,980
We always text each other,

586
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,780
like what time
we should wake up tomorrow,

587
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:43,360
when it starts, when we should arrive.

588
00:28:43,380 --> 00:28:45,480
We also text to go hang out
and eat together.

589
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:48,120
Can't I have my eyelashes curled?

590
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,160
Look at how we live, honey.

591
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:51,720
You should go bared-face.

592
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:55,820
Too pretty and you'll be
putting yourself in danger, you know?

593
00:28:56,780 --> 00:29:00,360
Next time,
bring five extra personal cameras.

594
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:05,540
All on you.

595
00:29:05,580 --> 00:29:12,340
You can act
and have 5 angles on you at once.

596
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:13,800
(How do you feel?)

597
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:27,620
I think P'Nui fits this role well.

598
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:28,860
I kind of admire her.

599
00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:35,600
She also hosts a show,
so she speaks very clearly.

600
00:29:36,320 --> 00:29:40,800
And P'Captain, I really like him too.

601
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:42,700
He starred in Ban Ni Mi Rak sitcom.

602
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:46,280
He feels like a father figure to me.

603
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:49,020
When we act in scenes together,
it feels really close.

604
00:29:49,060 --> 00:29:51,000
So I'm happy.

605
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:55,760
When we rehearse,
he goes through the lines with me.

606
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:58,380
He repeats my previous lines,

607
00:29:58,420 --> 00:30:01,620
like feeding me the cues
so I can continue.

608
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:04,660
I feel like that's very professional,
and I find it really impressive.

609
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,400
Very good.

610
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:13,400
Want an orange tree at your place?

611
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:14,380
You seem to like them a lot.

612
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:17,140
I only like the one next door. That's all.

613
00:30:18,700 --> 00:30:25,640
This series is about a group of students
who come together,

614
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:32,100
having fun, doing activities,
going through things together,

615
00:30:32,140 --> 00:30:33,580
and living life together.

616
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:35,580
There are many stories
that happen along the way.

617
00:30:35,620 --> 00:30:38,740
It's warm and nostalgic,
like going back to the '90s.

618
00:30:38,780 --> 00:30:41,140
The setting is in the '90s,

619
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:46,260
so you'll get to see the development
of Ko Neung and Ko Song's relationship.

620
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:50,100
I understand what '90s were like.

621
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:54,840
I've seen many films from that era.

622
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,520
I think it would be really fun,

623
00:30:56,700 --> 00:31:04,420
going out to play with friends every day
since there were no phones to use—

624
00:31:04,460 --> 00:31:06,400
no calling each other
to play games online,

625
00:31:06,420 --> 00:31:07,560
so we'd run around
and play outside instead.

626
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:12,080
My dad told me about it himself
what games people played back in the '90s.

627
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,620
That thing—what do you call it?

628
00:31:13,660 --> 00:31:16,380
The one with rubber bands,
tied and woven together, and you shoot it.

629
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:18,860
The way people talked was different too.

630
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:21,200
People these days
probably don't say "Fly," right?

631
00:31:21,860 --> 00:31:24,340
Back then, they'd say,
"Hey, that's so fly."

632
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:31,860
As for me, I watched movies from that era
to see what people did in their free time,

633
00:31:31,900 --> 00:31:35,800
where they liked to go,
and what they liked to do.

634
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:38,400
What kind of hobbies people had back then.

635
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,200
There was listening to cassette tapes.

636
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:43,220
I think I'd be reading comics
if I lived in that time.

637
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:47,760
These days, I scroll TikTok
and use Instagram,

638
00:31:48,060 --> 00:31:52,100
but back then,
I'd probably be reading Dragon Ball,

639
00:31:52,340 --> 00:31:53,640
just like in the series.

640
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:56,500
Without phones,
what did people do back then?

641
00:31:56,740 --> 00:31:59,540
They told me they played games
like rubber band jumping

642
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:03,360
and traditional Thai games like Ri Ri Khaosan.

643
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:09,720
It actually sounds fun,
with that old-school vibe.

644
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:12,520
No need to be glued
to your phone all the time,

645
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:16,840
just being with friends
and living in the moment together.

646
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,120
When we were filming on set,

647
00:32:19,140 --> 00:32:26,480
the desks were wooden, really solid,
with that brown color.

648
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:30,780
But nowadays, schools use newer desks.

649
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:35,760
The art team managed to find old-style desks
for the whole classroom.

650
00:32:36,100 --> 00:32:36,920
I think that's really cool.

651
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:40,800
And each old desk
had correction fluid scribbles on it.

652
00:32:40,860 --> 00:32:42,300
The art team did an amazing job.

653
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:44,420
There were writings
carved on the desks too.

654
00:32:44,460 --> 00:32:45,140
True.

655
00:32:45,180 --> 00:32:48,020
And I also like the locations.

656
00:32:48,220 --> 00:32:49,260
Yes.

657
00:32:49,380 --> 00:32:51,460
It feels like
we don't have to imagine much.

658
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:54,580
As soon as we step in,
it already feels like the '90s.

659
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:59,600
There are photos, flags,
it just feels right.

660
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:03,240
Yeah, the moment we walk into the school,
as soon as we look around,

661
00:33:04,260 --> 00:33:06,020
it's like, this is it, exactly right.

662
00:33:13,540 --> 00:33:15,580
What are you planning to do
after high school?

663
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,960
I haven't really figured that out yet.

664
00:33:18,020 --> 00:33:18,840
What about you?

665
00:33:18,900 --> 00:33:20,180
Maybe med school.

666
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:21,940
Then I'll go to the same university as you.

667
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:25,800
We'll wrap up here.

668
00:33:27,020 --> 00:33:28,180
(Not yet, we just started filming.)

669
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:32,020
Oh, then the next scene is with…

670
00:33:32,340 --> 00:33:35,860
Augar and August, Ko Song, Ko Kae.

671
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:37,440
(Where's Ko Neung?)

672
00:33:37,460 --> 00:33:39,720
No Ko Neung. He's a director.

673
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,020
It was fun.

674
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:45,480
I like hanging out with the crew on set.

675
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,480
He went and unplugged the monitor

676
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:48,340
I didn't do that.

677
00:33:48,780 --> 00:33:51,700
and also adjusted the camera focus.

678
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:55,160
He dipped the wireless mic into water.

679
00:33:55,180 --> 00:33:57,480
No, I never did that. That's a no-no.

680
00:33:57,500 --> 00:33:58,620
It's expensive.

681
00:33:59,980 --> 00:34:02,000
Those were the things Progress…

682
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:04,180
-…didn't do.
-I did one of those—

683
00:34:04,380 --> 00:34:06,100
adjusting the focus.

684
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:09,000
There's always someone inviting me
to do something.

685
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:10,920
Ken asks me to chat or take a nap.

686
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:15,700
Progress asks me to go for a walk,
he likes walking around,

687
00:34:16,060 --> 00:34:17,020
and messing with people.

688
00:34:17,060 --> 00:34:20,020
I mean, he doesn't invite me
to mess with others, he messes with me,

689
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:21,540
and even gets others to join in teasing me.

690
00:34:21,580 --> 00:34:25,780
Almond asks me to ride a scooter.

691
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,220
He's into speed.

692
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:37,220
On set, there are bicycles,
and the location team has electric bikes.

693
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:39,420
Almond rides them really fast.

694
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:42,420
That's probably
the only playful thing he does.

695
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:45,820
He's a real speedster.

696
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:50,620
Almond on set is quiet
and doesn't talk much.

697
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:53,620
When he's fully awake,

698
00:34:54,020 --> 00:34:55,060
he talks more,

699
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:59,600
but he likes having his own space
and often seems sleepy.

700
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:01,440
During breaks,
he always has his skateboard.

701
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:05,100
He rides it all around the school.

702
00:35:05,180 --> 00:35:08,300
-(Come on. Time to film your scene.)
-I don't want to go.

703
00:35:08,580 --> 00:35:10,420
Don't make me go.

704
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,780
-(Wake up!)
-No~

705
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:14,400
No~

706
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,220
(Wake up!)

707
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:16,600
We end up not sleeping.

708
00:35:18,620 --> 00:35:22,640
The last time we filmed a beach scene,
they convinced each other not to sleep.

709
00:35:22,660 --> 00:35:24,360
I only got an hour and a half of sleep.

710
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:27,600
But somehow, with just that much sleep,
I felt even more energized.

711
00:35:27,620 --> 00:35:29,240
My energy was overflowing,

712
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:31,060
even more than on days
when I get enough sleep.

713
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:32,040
I don't know why.

714
00:35:32,260 --> 00:35:34,120
On days I sleep well,
I still feel like sleeping more,

715
00:35:34,140 --> 00:35:39,340
but on days I don't get enough sleep,
I somehow have even more energy.

716
00:35:39,380 --> 00:35:41,140
So I kind of force myself,

717
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:43,080
and my energy ends up
overflowing even more.

718
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:48,320
Since we're all boys,
it feels really fun while filming.

719
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:52,640
If we run out of things to say in a scene,
P'Progress would improvise, like,

720
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:54,020
"Hey, Western kid—"

721
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:57,460
So it was fun and made the scene
even more enjoyable.

722
00:35:57,780 --> 00:36:00,340
It was chaotic, pretty chaotic.

723
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:04,900
Especially in the sports scenes,

724
00:36:05,020 --> 00:36:07,380
we played hard and went all out.

725
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:12,440
I was soaked in sweat,
and had to wait a long time to dry off.

726
00:36:12,740 --> 00:36:16,400
Every night, when my light goes out,
my window slowly lights up.

727
00:36:16,460 --> 00:36:17,420
Ko!

728
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:18,960
Whenever I have a problem,

729
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:21,160
you're always that light.

730
00:36:22,540 --> 00:36:24,120
That's how I really feel.

731
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:34,360
The OST for this series—

732
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:37,940
It's a song we put our whole hearts into.

733
00:36:37,980 --> 00:36:42,360
I think everyone has already heard it,
since it's in the trailer.

734
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:45,360
Yes. It's in the trailer.

735
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,700
Yes, I sang the chorus key.

736
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,240
It's my first time singing in that key.

737
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:51,500
I've never sung in this key before,
so it was quite difficult,

738
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:54,540
but I managed to get through it well.

739
00:36:54,900 --> 00:36:59,220
The song title is exactly
what everyone's been waiting for,

740
00:36:59,260 --> 00:37:01,420
it's called Worth the Wait.

741
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:04,020
Just like how everyone has been waiting
for this series from Almond and Progress.

742
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:05,880
I've seen a lot of comments,
it's not like I haven't,

743
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:08,780
I've seen them from all the fans.

744
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,680
It will definitely be worth the wait.

745
00:37:11,220 --> 00:37:11,800
That's right.

746
00:37:20,580 --> 00:37:21,740
Breath in.

747
00:37:23,180 --> 00:37:24,620
Shift your eyes a little, then say…

748
00:37:25,560 --> 00:37:26,660
"What do you mean?"

749
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:27,880
What do you mean?

750
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:37,100
See for yourself, those who think
Almond and Progress aren't chaotic.

751
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:44,300
At first, I thought P'New
would be a strict director.

752
00:37:44,620 --> 00:37:48,140
I thought I'd definitely get scolded
when I came on set.

753
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:52,920
But… he's really chill, very chill.

754
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:55,920
He's a lovely director,
caring and attentive,

755
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:58,640
and you can talk to him about anything.

756
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:01,100
I feel like I'm in my safe zone,
like being with my dad.

757
00:38:01,740 --> 00:38:03,500
P'New is really like my dad,

758
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:07,820
his face, the way he dresses,
the same style.

759
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:10,440
P'New is exactly like my father.

760
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,940
I feel like it's very easy to connect
when working with him.

761
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:15,960
He's someone
you can talk to about anything,

762
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:19,320
just like my dad,
I can say anything to him.

763
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:21,160
He really is like my dad.

764
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:25,080
I feel like he's very skilled
at directing,

765
00:38:25,140 --> 00:38:27,480
and he pays great attention to each scene.

766
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:30,840
Actually, most people on this set
are pretty chill,

767
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:33,640
very friendly and lovely.

768
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:36,440
That was too high, "I'm trying."

769
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:37,680
Lower your voice.

770
00:38:37,700 --> 00:38:40,260
"I'm trying."

771
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:41,760
I'm trying.

772
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:42,940
Then throw a punch.

773
00:38:43,500 --> 00:38:44,360
Make it clean and clear.

774
00:38:44,380 --> 00:38:46,200
Because it's your punch that makes him…

775
00:38:47,180 --> 00:38:49,080
Progress, what did you do to Paul earlier?

776
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,840
Paul!

777
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,760
-I'm falling, Paul.
-Achi, don't do this to my dad.

778
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,960
I'm falling, Paul.

779
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:00,760
Achi, don't do this to my dad.

780
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:07,440
The crew and director are super kind.

781
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:12,460
I was really happy when I went on set.
I could be myself 100%.

782
00:39:12,500 --> 00:39:13,940
I miss you to the moon and back.

783
00:39:13,980 --> 00:39:14,600
I don't believe you.

784
00:39:14,620 --> 00:39:17,420
♪ Though I always ask if you love me too ♪

785
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:20,160
Actually, all the locations
aren't in Bangkok.

786
00:39:20,180 --> 00:39:22,040
It was fun.

787
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:24,720
It was exhausting but fun,
so the tiredness just went away.

788
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:26,520
I got to be with my friends.

789
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:27,960
It felt more like I was on holiday.

790
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:31,480
P'New is really kind, and he's friendly.

791
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:34,000
He took us out to eat and explore around.

792
00:39:34,240 --> 00:39:36,600
What will viewers get
from watching this series?

793
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:42,140
It's about teenage relationships
that many people may have experienced.

794
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:45,160
And since it's set in the '90s,
everyone will get to go back to that time.

795
00:39:45,180 --> 00:39:47,260
I like it, I enjoy going back
to that era too.

796
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:49,760
Everyone will get to feel
the '90s vibe again.

797
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:56,280
What viewers will get, I think,
is the feeling of the old time.

798
00:39:56,320 --> 00:40:01,560
Being a kid, you don't have to
think too much about anything,

799
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:04,140
including relationships.

800
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:07,180
You just stick with someone
because you enjoy being with them,

801
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:09,580
just having fun together
is enough to be happy.

802
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:11,460
There's no need to overthink.

803
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:16,040
I feel like that's something
viewers will really like.

804
00:40:16,220 --> 00:40:17,500
This series?

805
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:22,280
I think it's a high school story
about a group of friends.

806
00:40:22,300 --> 00:40:27,980
It has that fun, youthful energy
that makes it enjoyable to watch.

807
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:34,320
This one has just been really fun for me.

808
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:39,760
It has the boyhood vibe,
the '90s, the humor.

809
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:40,640
It's definitely funny.

810
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:44,900
Another thing viewers will get
is the friendship within the group.

811
00:40:44,940 --> 00:40:49,560
After watching, you might miss
your school friends,

812
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,280
or if you're still in school,

813
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:55,640
you might appreciate
your friends even more.

814
00:40:55,900 --> 00:40:59,160
I want everyone to grow along with us.

815
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:02,820
There's also a storyline
that makes the series interesting.

816
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:09,840
The '90s mood takes viewers back
to that time in the past.

817
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:13,080
The mood and tone are really good.

818
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:16,360
Even I feel the mood is great.

819
00:41:16,380 --> 00:41:18,640
I wish I could live in that time too.

820
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:22,220
That one pretty pose there, Ko.

821
00:41:22,660 --> 00:41:24,880
-You want a piece of me?
-Teacher!

822
00:41:24,900 --> 00:41:26,520
He put his leg down.

823
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:29,000
You can't do that.

824
00:41:30,020 --> 00:41:34,440
Please look forward to August,
as well as me, Justin.

825
00:41:34,780 --> 00:41:37,180
I gave this series everything I had.

826
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:39,960
It's my first project with GMMTV,

827
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:43,800
and I'm really happy
to have this opportunity.

828
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:50,860
Everyone worked very hard on this series,
so I hope you'll come watch it.

829
00:41:51,020 --> 00:41:55,600
Please show some love
to the character Tle.

830
00:41:55,620 --> 00:41:58,600
This is my first project with GMMTV.

831
00:41:58,620 --> 00:42:00,560
I hope everyone will like it.

832
00:42:00,620 --> 00:42:05,400
I did my best to make this character
as fun as possible.

833
00:42:05,500 --> 00:42:11,180
Please support When Oranges Fall too.

834
00:42:11,940 --> 00:42:13,640
Please check out my character, Augar.

835
00:42:13,680 --> 00:42:16,940
Please support and cheer
for this character too.

836
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:20,400
Let's see what kind of kid Augar is,

837
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:21,720
what he does,

838
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:22,860
and how the story unfolds.

839
00:42:22,980 --> 00:42:24,680
Please root for this character.

840
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:26,420
And support all the characters as well.

841
00:42:26,460 --> 00:42:27,920
Everyone has their own unique personality.

842
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:30,540
This series is definitely going to be fun.

843
00:42:30,660 --> 00:42:32,660
Please give my character, Achi, some love too.

844
00:42:32,680 --> 00:42:34,820
He's a really lovely character.

845
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:36,600
He starts off very cute,

846
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:41,400
but let's see, with this gang of friends,
whether he'll stay this adorable.

847
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:44,660
Let's grow together with them.

848
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:51,500
Please look forward to Ko Song
and When Oranges Fall.

849
00:42:51,540 --> 00:42:53,020
I want everyone to follow along

850
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:55,900
and see how the relationship
between Ko Song and Ko Neung unfolds.

851
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:57,040
We all poured our hearts into this

852
00:42:57,060 --> 00:43:00,120
and we really want everyone
to come watch it.

853
00:43:00,260 --> 00:43:04,920
Once you watch When Oranges Fall,

854
00:43:05,060 --> 00:43:10,200
you'll get that '90s mood,
with great visuals and color tones.

855
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:13,580
Please show some love to Ko Neung too.

856
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:18,260
I put a lot of effort into it,
as did everyone else.

857
00:43:18,580 --> 00:43:19,820
We really want you
to come check out the series.

858
00:43:19,980 --> 00:43:21,260
"The orange tree is in his yard,

859
00:43:21,300 --> 00:43:24,140
but its oranges
keep falling into my yard."

860
00:43:26,920 --> 00:43:30,780
